      <h1 class="text-center">About Pantry App</h1>
      <p class="text-center text-secondary mt-3">
        Welcome to the Pantry App! This application allows you to manage your
        pantry items efficiently. Here, you can add, edit, delete, and view
        items with ease. Below is a detailed explanation of the features and
        functionality of the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-4">Features</h2>
      <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Add Items:</strong> You can add new items to your pantry by
          providing details like name, price, quantity, and an image of the
          item.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Edit Items:</strong> If you need to update any details of an
          existing item, you can easily do so by editing the item.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Delete Items:</strong> You can remove items from your pantry
          that are no longer needed.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>View Items:</strong> All the items in your pantry are
          displayed in a table format, making it easy to view and manage them.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Notifications:</strong> The app provides notifications for
          actions like adding, updating, or deleting items.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-4">Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Frontend:</strong> The frontend of the app is built using EJS
          for templating, along with Bootstrap for styling.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Backend:</strong> The backend is powered by Express.js, a
          minimal and flexible Node.js web application framework.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Database:</strong> MongoDB is used as the database to store
          pantry items.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>File Uploads:</strong> Multer is used for handling
          multipart/form-data, which is primarily used for uploading files.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-4">Usage</h2>
      <p>To use the Pantry App, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Adding an Item:</strong> Navigate to the "Add Item" page and
          fill in the details of the item you want to add. Upload an image if
          available and submit the form.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Editing an Item:</strong> On the homepage, click the edit icon
          next to the item you want to update. Make the necessary changes and
          submit the form.
        </li>
        <li class="list-group-item">
          <strong>Deleting an Item:</strong> On the homepage, click the delete
          icon next to the item you want to remove. Confirm the deletion to
          remove the item from your pantry.
        </li>
      </ol>

